documentation.author: Karen Speaks
documentation.purpose: Ticket 390750 rule to print a expedite report for following critical lab results for IP/observation/ED hold patients and have discharge location on the report. Associated Scripts: bc_eks_specimen_type: CCL script to set results with specimen type; parameter "CSF"> link is required bc_eks_micro_positive: CCL script to set results with positive micro; no parameter > link is requried bc_eks_print_expedite_lab: CL script to print lab report; parameters ouput(printer/file/email addr must include @baycare.org), report_type("MICRO" or "LAB"), 0.0 > link is required ; executes bc_pc_rpt_expedite_lab_lo
documentation.explanation:
IP/Observation/ER Hold Discharged Critical Results Log A. Gen Lab 1. Labs with Critical Value flag 2. Bordetella Pert/Para PCR (all specimen type): Abnormal Normalcy 3. Cryptococcus Ag (specimen type: CSF): Abnormal Normalcy 4. HSV 1+2 PCR (specimen type: CSF): Abnormal Normalcy 5. HSV/VZV Panel by PCR (specimen type: CSF): Abnormal Normalcy 6. VZV PCR (specimen type: CSF): Abnormal Normalcy 7. Pneumococcal Ag Urine/CSF (specimen type: CSF): Abnormal Normalcy 8. CMV PCR QUALITATIVE (specimen type: CSF): Abnormal Normalcy
B. Micro Labs 1. Blood Culture (all specimen type): Positive Indicator 2. CSF Culture (all specimen type): Positive indicator 3. AFB Culture (all specimen type): Positive indicator 4. AFB Stain (all specimen type): Positive Normalcy 5. Candida Panel Blood (all specimen type): Positive Normalcy 6. EBV PCR Quantitative (Specimen type: CSF): Positive Normalcy
documentation.keywords: expedite labs critical Bordetella Pert/Para PCR Cryptococcus Ag HSV 1+2 PCR HSV/VZV Panel by PCR VZV PCR Pneumococcal Ag Urine CMV PCR QUALITATIV Blood Culture CSF Culture AFB Culture AFB Stain Candida Panel Blood EBV PCR Quantitative

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_DEBUGEKM_E
templateDefinitions.description: Turn debug messaging on or off

statements.statement:
select debug_status = if (d.seq = 1) "On for subsequent Evoke Templates" elseif (d.seq = 2) "Off for subsequent Evoke Templates" elseif (d.seq = 3) "On for all Logic Templates" elseif (d.seq = 4) "On for all Action Templates" elseif (d.seq = 5) "On for all Logic and Action Templates" elseif (d.seq = 6) "To FullAudit for this module only" elseif (d.seq = 7) "Additional EKSDATA logging" ENDIF, _hidden = if (d.seq = 1) 1 elseif (d.seq=2) 0 elseif (d.seq=3) 2 elseif (d.seq=4) 3 elseif (d.seq=5) 4 elseif (d.seq=6) 5 elseif (d.seq=7) 6 endif
FROM (DUMMYT D WITH SEQ = VALUE(7))

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_CE_RESULT_STATUS_E
templateDefinitions.definition: EVENT_SET_NAME is in any of the statuses listed: STATUS

statements.statement:
eks_event_set_name_refhelp PAR1, "EVENT_SET" go
/* SELECT IF (PAR1="*ANY") EVENT_SET_NAME="*ANY_EVENT_SET_NAME" ELSEIF (PAR1="ALL") EVENT_SET_NAME = V.EVENT_SET_NAME FROM V500_EVENT_SET_CODE V ORDER cnvtupper(V.EVENT_SET_NAME) ELSEIF (PAR1 != "OTHER") EVENT_SET_NAME = V.EVENT_SET_NAME FROM V500_EVENT_SET_CODE V WHERE CNVTUPPER(V.EVENT_SET_NAME) =PATSTRING(CONCAT(cnvtupper(PAR1),"*")) ORDER cnvtupper(V.EVENT_SET_NAME) ELSE EVENT_SET_NAME= V.EVENT_SET_NAME FROM V500_EVENT_SET_CODE V WHERE CNVTUPPER(substring(1,1,V.EVENT_SET_NAME)) NOT BETWEEN "0" AND "Z" ORDER cnvtupper(V.EVENT_SET_NAME) ENDIF */

eks_codeset_cki_refhelp "8","CKI","*ANY_STATUS" go /* select distinct Result_Status = if (t.seq = 1) cv.description else "*ANY_STATUS" endif, _hidden = if (t.seq = 1) cv.code_value else 0.0 endif from code_value cv, (dummyt t with seq=2) plan cv where cv.code_set = 8 and cv.active_ind = 1 and cv.cdf_meaning > " " join t order Result_Status */
